:::: See ``/twelf/examples/lp/test.cfg`` for the only significant code I broke banning Thaw. If you've frozen your language of atoms and you now need more atoms, you can declare them dynamically, which is an enormous mess in this example, or you can just thaw your base atom type knowing you're justified by the way you wrote all your ``[%block](/wiki/percent-block/)`` and ``[%worlds](/wiki/percent-worlds/)`` directives. — [User:rsimmons](/wiki/user-rsimmons/) (and his [User talk:rsimmons](/wiki/user-talk-rsimmons/)) 12:49, 28 February 2007 (EST)
